Defendant Melissa P Calvert in court with attorney Marcella De Peters.  Denis John Stingl appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
AS TO COUNT 4:  Defendant ordered to serve 1 year in the House of Correction with credit of 73 days time served.  Court STAYED the sentence and placed the defendant on probation for 2 years with the following Maintain absolute sobriety.  Defendant only to take prescribed medication as prescribed.
Court ordered defendant to pay all applicable court costs and surcharges by over the duration of probation or, if not paid, a civil judgment will be ordered.
Defendant shall provide a DNA sample for the Data Bank and pay all appropriate costs over the duration of probation.
NO CONTACT ORDER REMAINS WITH CODEFENDANT.
Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon he may never possess a firearm or body armor. Court advised defendant that her voting rights are suspended and she may not vote in any election until her civil rights are restored. 
